Citation.sTitle: (p, rho, T) Properties and Apparent Molar Volumes V(phi) of ZnCl2 in CH3OH
Citation.sAbstract: The (p, rho, T) properties and apparent molar volumes V of ZnCl2 in methanol at T = (298.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to p = 40 MPa are reported. An empirical correlation for the density of the (ZnCl2 + CH3OH) with pressure, temperature, and molality has been derived. For the solutions the experiments were carried out at molalities m = (0.13476, 0.47677, 0.80178, 1.03861, 1.97685, and 5.36750) mol*kg-1 of zinc chloride.
Citation.sKeyword: T) properties and apparent molar volumes V of ZnCl2 in methanol
